The UI architecture of **OmniCalc Pro** is built on a philosophy of **"Vibe Coding"**—combining glassmorphism, mathematical precision, and high-frequency motion design. As a Lead UI Architect, I’ve implemented a design system that prioritizes a "premium dark" aesthetic often found in high-end financial terminals.

Here is the breakdown of the design system with the core code driving it:

### 1. The Foundation: Atmospheric Depth
Instead of flat backgrounds, we use a **Dynamic Mesh Gradient**. This creates a sense of "living" software that isn't static.

```css
/* From index.html */
.bg-mesh {
  position: fixed;
  inset: -50%;
  z-index: -1;
  background: radial-gradient(circle at 30% 30%, var(--accent-glow) 0%, transparent 50%),
              radial-gradient(circle at 70% 70%, rgba(244, 63, 94, 0.04) 0%, transparent 50%);
  filter: blur(100px);
  animation: mesh-movement 30s ease-in-out infinite alternate;
}
```

### 2. The Surface: Glassmorphism (Aero Style)
Every container uses a "Glass" layer. This provides visual hierarchy through translucency rather than just color changes.

```css
/* Defined in index.html, used in DesktopView.tsx */
.glass {
  background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.02); /* Very subtle white tint */
  backdrop-filter: blur(24px);           /* The "Aero" effect */
  border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06); /* Sharp "Expensive" edge */
  transition: all 0.4s cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1);
}

.glass:hover {
  background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.04);
  border-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.12); /* Interactive glow */
}
```

### 3. The Motion Signature: Fluid Entrances
Static layouts feel "cheap." We use **Staggered Fade-Ups** to make the UI feel like it's assembling itself.

```javascript
/* Logic used in CalculatorForm.tsx and ResultsView.tsx */
{results.map((res, idx) => (
  <div 
    key={res.id} 
    className="animate-fade-up"
    style={{ animationDelay: `${idx * 0.1}s` }} // Staggered delay for "Cascade" effect
  >
    {/* Content */}
  </div>
))}
```

### 4. Mathematical Precision: Dual-Type System
We use two distinct fonts to separate "Information" from "Data":
*   **Plus Jakarta Sans:** For UI labels and descriptions (Human-centric).
*   **JetBrains Mono:** For calculations, results, and timers (Machine-centric).

```tsx
/* From ResultsView.tsx */
<div className="text-[10px] font-black uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-slate-500">
  {res.label} {/* UI Label: Plus Jakarta Sans */}
</div>

<div className="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight mono">
  {res.value} {/* Result Data: JetBrains Mono */}
</div>
```

### 5. Micro-Interactions: 3D Layering
The `CalculatorLogo.tsx` uses a **3D Offset Pattern** to create tactile depth without complex WebGL.

```tsx
/* From CalculatorLogo.tsx */
<div className="relative group">
  {/* Shadow Layer: Provides 3D depth */}
  <div className="absolute inset-0 bg-indigo-800 rounded-[2.5rem] translate-y-4 transition-transform"></div>

  {/* Main Body: Moves "up" on hover, revealing the shadow below */}
  <div className="relative bg-indigo-500 rounded-[2.5rem] transform group-hover:-translate-y-2 transition-all">
    {/* Interactive contents */}
  </div>
</div>
```

### Summary of Design Tokens
*   **Primary Accent:** Indigo-600 (`#6366f1`).
*   **Base Neutral:** Slate-950 (`#020617`).
*   **Radius Strategy:** `3xl` (32px) for main containers, `xl` (16px) for inner elements.
*   **Visual Logic:** Calculation outputs are always highlighted with a glowing shadow (`shadow-xl shadow-accent/20`).
